
  Name:  mbstowcs
  
  #include <stdlib.h>
  size_t mbstowcs(wchar_t *out, const char *in, size_t size);

  The mbstowcs( ) function converts the multibyte string pointed
  to by in into a wide-character string and puts that result in
  the array pointed to by out. Only size number of bytes will be
  stored in out.
  
  Example:
  mbstowcs(str, mb, 4);
 
  Related Functions:  wcstombs and mbtowc

